Bank BPH, Egis, Lotos, Tauron: Central European Stock Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 
2011-05-10T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/bank-bph-egis-lotos-tauron-central-european-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 1.2 percent, the Czech PX Index
dropped 0.1 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index added 0.7 percent.  Bank BPH SA (BPH)  : The Polish financial unit of General
Electric Co. is scheduled to release first-quarter earnings. BPH
shares were unchanged at 73.1 zloty.  Egis Nyrt. (EGIS HB): The Hungarian drugmaker owned by
Laboratoires Servier said net profit fell 4 percent to 4.5
billion ($24.5 million), or 583 forint a share, in the first
quarter due to losses on financial activities. Egis gained 0.6
percent to 19,910 forint.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  : Poland’s second-largest oil
refiner will report earnings for the first quarter. Lotos
advanced 1.4 percent to 46.44 zloty.  Nova Kreditna Banka Maribor d.d. (KBMR SV): Slovenia’s
second-biggest bank will start trading on the  Warsaw Stock
Exchange . Its shares tumbled 3.7 percent to 8.67 euro in
Ljubljana trading.  Tauron Polska Energia SA (TPE)  : Poland’s second-largest
power utility will report first-quarter results. Tauron gained
0.8 percent to 6.22 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
